column5: Ya that would be nice as I leave in 4 hours

I've been catching numbers of eaters on small jig's tipped with a minnow or leach, both work. The larger fish seem to be coming on crankbaits, shadraps & hot n tots. The biggest fish was from the goon, although we did get some respectable fish in the smaller lakes as well.fish on!
Anybody go to the goon yet. How's the fishing
Limited out off the dock tonight. Limited on 16 to 18"ers and released a 22"er.They are still in shallow.
fisherman 1 (or anyone else who knows)- What is the lake level like now? Heard it was down quite a bit after ice out.
I'd like to know how low the water is myself.
Water level on Wabigoon is near normal. Winds calm walleye waiting! Out I go..
These fish are ALWAYS shallow!!!Go get 'em guys!!
Ok, T minus 5 days to departure Anyone have any current reports on Wabigoon? Any reports and/or tips would be very much apprecaited!
The bite has been good! About 8' of water off of the points and humps have been producing lots of fish! Had a great day today, lots of eaters and a 31"er and a 27.Both released!
Thanks fisherman1!!!Are you fishing Wabigoon or the other surrounding lakes?What have you been using for bait/presentation?Again, THANKS!!!!
